OL,6,FBut this is very different to
OL,7,Fsuggestions of subscription funding,
OL,8,Fdirect government funding or
OL,9,Fadvertising.
OL,11,FRather the question is whether there
OL,12,Fmight be a way of making the fee
OL,13,Ffairer and how to ensure those who
OL,14,Fdon't have TV sets can stop taking
OL,15,Fadvantage of BBC content for free.
OL,17,FAs I said last week, the mood music
OL,18,Faround the BBC's future is likely to
OL,19,Fbe very different if Labour is in
OL,20,Fpower after the General Election.
